          {
            "commit": "88f2129504f0530106ebdbe7f5ff918d03bfcb42",
            "subject": "LU-5912 libcfs: use vfs api for fsync calls"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Cheng Shao",
          "email": "cheng_shao@xyratex.com",
          "date": "2015-02-10 17:28:25.000000000",
          "tz": -480
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Jian Yu",
          "email": "jian.yu@intel.com",
          "date": "2015-02-10 17:28:25.000000000",
          "tz": -480
        },
        "subject": "LU-4582 mgc: replace hard-coded MGC_ENQUEUE_LIMIT value",
        "message": "LU-4582 mgc: replace hard-coded MGC_ENQUEUE_LIMIT value\n\nDuring client mount, the client will send an LDLM_ENQUEUE request to\nMGS with send delay set to MGC_ENQUEUE_LIMIT, which is hard coded to\n50 seconds. On the other hand, the interval for pinger is deduced from\nobd_timeout. When obd_timeout is configured for a longer period of\ntime, so does the pinger. We know that connecting to the secondary MGS\nnode is triggered by the pinger. Now that we have a longer interval,\nthe pinger will not be able to try the secondary before the\nLDLM_ENQUEUE request fails the mount using the same delay limit.\n\nThis code change will replace the hard-coded send delay being\nmentioned above with a value that is long enough to give the client a\nchance to connect to the secondary MGS if exists.\n\nThis patch is back-ported from the following one:\nLustre-commit: fb7ac6a880b71cb9e0252bcbb6d9bbb4b4ddf7fd\nLustre-change: http://review.whamcloud.com/9217\n\nXyratex-bug-id: MRP-1516\n\nSigned-off-by: Cheng Shao <cheng_shao@xyratex.com>\nChange-Id: I3490552b54d7978fe63478951bb166b77254dc3d\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/b2_5"
    }
  },
